We use the identity $\sin x = \cos(90^\circ - x)$. Then
$$\sin n^\circ = \cos(90^\circ - n^\circ).$$

So, we want to find $n$ such that $\sin n^\circ = \cos 96^\circ$.

Therefore, we need $\sin n^\circ = -\sin 6^\circ$.

So $n = -174$ or $n = 186 - 360 = -174$.

Since the cosine function has period $360^\circ,$
\[\cos 456^\circ = \cos (456^\circ - 360^\circ) = \cos 96^\circ.\]Since $\cos x = \sin (90^\circ - x)$ for all angles $x,$
